i'm trying to save an xslx file with FileSaver, which works on chrome but fails on FF (corrupt data)

here's waht i use:

```
var b64toBlob = function(b64Data, contentType, sliceSize) {
      contentType = contentType || '';
      sliceSize = sliceSize || 512;
      var byteCharacters = atob(b64Data);
      var byteArrays = [];
      for (var offset = 0; offset < byteCharacters.length; offset += sliceSize) {
        var slice = byteCharacters.slice(offset, offset + sliceSize);
        var byteNumbers = new Array(slice.length);
        for (var i = 0; i < slice.length; i++) {
          byteNumbers[i] = slice.charCodeAt(i);
        }
        var byteArray = new Uint8Array(byteNumbers);
        byteArrays.push(byteArray);
      }
      var blob = new Blob(byteArrays, {type: contentType});
      return blob;
    }
    var excel = EB.createFile(workbook).then(function(data) {
      var blob = b64toBlob(data, 'application/octet-stream');
      saveAs(blob, 'Film-Sammler_' + moment().format('DD.MM.YYYY__HH.mm.ss') + '.xlsx');
    });
```

it seems the blob gets corrupted while on FF, maybe a size Problem (i have about 350rows here, ~950kb data)

anybody an idea?

is there anyway to tell the echo to "talk" outside of forcing it in the function return?

@ask.intent("SleepIntent")
def sleepy_time():
    os.system("rundll32.exe powrprof.dll,SetSuspendState 0,1,0")
    msg = render_template('sleep')
    return statement(msg) 

See the above function. what is happening here (when I call this function) is the machine is instantly falling asleep, and its never making it to the end of the function to read the string in, and therefore never triggers the return.

what i tried doing was breaking it out into two functions, so the sleep function calls the sleep talk function. I wanted to call it, have the verbal response go through the echo, then jump back to the calling function and continue on with the sleep, but this doesnt work. If I enter in debug statements, I can see that the sleep function, does call sleep talk function, but still nothing is heard prior to the sleep.

def sleepy_time_talk():
    msg = render_template('sleep')
    return statement(msg) 

@ask.intent("SleepIntent")
def sleepy_time():
    sleepy_time_talk()
    os.system("rundll32.exe powrprof.dll,SetSuspendState 0,1,0")

